stimulus_2.text:
The students at a primary school were lined up.

At the front of the line were three boys, then three girls, then three boys and so on.

Mary is a girl and is standing 24th in the line.

Her brother Peter is also in the line.

In what position can Peter not be standing in?

review_3.column_1_text: Draw a table to help see the arrangement:

review_5.column_1_text:
From the table, you can see that it is possible for Peter to be standing 26th, 27th or 37th in the line.

Peter cannot be standing in the 36th position.

Tip

Sometimes you can find the correct answer by checking each of the choices given in the question.

success.question_text: What would be the 23rd digit after the decimal point?
success.question_category_path: Numeracy / Algebra, Function and Patterns / Patterns

stimulus_3.text:
He can see that the digits are repeating.

The sixth digit after the decimal point is a 5.

review_3.column_1_text:
In 0.7142857142857 … a group of 6 digits are repeating.

So every sixth digit will be a 5.

This means that the 24th digit is a 5.

The 23rd digit will be in the place before 5.

The 23rd digit would be an 8.

Tip

stimulus_1.text: Kahlia wrote out the odd numbers in a pattern of rows and columns.

review_3.column_1_text:
If the pattern is continued the 20s and 30s are in Row B, the 40s and 50s will be in Row C and the 60s and 70s in Row D.

So 73 will be in Row D.

Numbers ending in 3 are in Columns b and g.

63 will be in Column b and 73 will be in Column g.

The number 73 will be in Row D Column g.

Tip

Sometimes the easiest way to find a particular term of a pattern is to just continue the pattern.

success.question_text: Which is not a step in the pattern?
success.question_category_path: Numeracy / Algebra, Function and Patterns / Number Patterns

stimulus_1.text: Here are some steps in a pattern:

review_3.column_1_text:
In each step the second number is the same as the step number.

The first number is three times the step number.

The last number is twice the step number.

So Step 7 is 21 – 7 = 14.

Step 12 is 36 – 12 = 24.

Step 17 is 51 – 17 = 34.

Step 21 is 63 – 21 = 42.

So 65 – 21 = 44 is not a step in the pattern.

Tip

The rule must work for all steps in the pattern.
